01:03:51,880 --> 01:03:53,630
-Yes, sir.
-Okay, what about it?

774
01:03:53,720 --> 01:03:56,300
I haven't done divorce cases in a while.

775
01:03:56,390 --> 01:03:57,390
-Right.
-And usually,

776
01:03:57,470 --> 01:03:59,640
clients prefer
female attorneys with divorces.

777
01:04:04,850 --> 01:04:07,270
Since when do you say
you don't want to do something?

778
01:04:08,730 --> 01:04:10,940
It's not that I don't want to do it.

779
01:04:11,030 --> 01:04:13,780
-For various reasons, instead of--
-I get what you're saying.

780
01:04:13,860 --> 01:04:16,200
But the client, Cha Jeongho,

781
01:04:16,950 --> 01:04:20,700
specifically requested a male attorney,
so we don't have a choice.

782
01:04:20,790 --> 01:04:25,040
-Then, that just leaves you.
-I see. He asked for a male attorney?

783
01:04:31,550 --> 01:04:34,260
-Do you want me to do it then?
-No.

784
01:04:35,590 --> 01:04:36,720
No, I should do it.

785
01:04:36,800 --> 01:04:38,760
-I appreciate it.
-Yes, sir.

786
01:05:05,200 --> 01:05:07,410
Right. Work is work.

787
01:05:18,010 --> 01:05:19,180
How are you feeling?

788
01:05:19,890 --> 01:05:21,930
I heard you woke up, so I came right away.

789
01:05:22,850 --> 01:05:25,850
Thank you. I'm feeling much better now.

790
01:05:26,560 --> 01:05:27,560
That's a relief.

791
01:05:28,810 --> 01:05:30,690
I heard Kim Sanggu

792
01:05:31,610 --> 01:05:33,610
claimed it was a ghost surgery?

793
01:05:34,610 --> 01:05:35,780
Yes.

794
01:05:35,860 --> 01:05:38,950
But I'm aware left-handed surgeons
often operate right-handed,

795
01:05:39,450 --> 01:05:42,450
so I can explain that part clearly.

796
01:05:44,870 --> 01:05:46,000
That's impressive.

797
01:05:46,830 --> 01:05:48,370
Most people don't know that.

798
01:05:51,380 --> 01:05:53,670
There was nothing wrong
with the surgery itself.

799
01:05:53,750 --> 01:05:56,090
But things like this
still seemed to happen.

800
01:05:57,380 --> 01:05:58,510
Every time it happens,

801
01:05:59,340 --> 01:06:02,550
I wonder if I'm actually saving lives
through surgery.

802
01:06:03,470 --> 01:06:05,390
If their deaths aren't my fault,

803
01:06:05,470 --> 01:06:08,600
maybe I shouldn't be get credit
for saving their lives either.

804
01:06:10,480 --> 01:06:12,310
That's why you wanted to apologize.

805
01:06:13,310 --> 01:06:15,070
But mustering the courage wasn't easy.

806
01:06:16,900 --> 01:06:19,110
I saw the look on your face back then.

807
01:06:19,200 --> 01:06:23,200
But an apology could be used
as evidence of negligence.

808
01:06:23,280 --> 01:06:25,450
That may not necessarily be the case.

809
01:06:25,530 --> 01:06:28,660
If there's no other evidence
of surgical malpractice,

810
01:06:28,750 --> 01:06:31,370
an apology alone isn't enough
to prove liability.

811
01:06:33,170 --> 01:06:35,170
I thought you'd be relieved
by what I said,

812
01:06:35,840 --> 01:06:37,340
but you looked surprised.

813
01:06:38,130 --> 01:06:40,380
I do believe I should apologize,

814
01:06:41,680 --> 01:06:43,680
but I just can't find
the courage to do it.

815
01:06:43,760 --> 01:06:49,270
Perhaps, a part of me felt at ease
when Mr. Kim tried to stop me.

816
01:06:49,350 --> 01:06:51,140
Please think about the hospital too.

817
01:06:51,230 --> 01:06:53,980
Because then,
it's not that I didn't apologize.

818
01:06:55,730 --> 01:06:57,400
I was stopped from doing it.

819
01:06:59,860 --> 01:07:03,110
I actually saw Kim Sanggu
on my way to court that day.

820
01:07:11,000 --> 01:07:12,290
I saw him.

821
01:07:14,250 --> 01:07:17,040
I couldn't even face him,
let alone apologize.

822
01:07:24,300 --> 01:07:25,800
I deserved to get ambushed.

823
01:07:26,930 --> 01:07:29,680
What's going to happen to him now?

824
01:07:31,100 --> 01:07:33,690
I heard he returned home.

825
01:07:34,310 --> 01:07:35,900
But he'll likely be indicted.

826
01:07:35,980 --> 01:07:36,980
If I…

827
01:07:38,230 --> 01:07:42,280
agree to settle,
will it reduce his punishment?

828
01:07:44,570 --> 01:07:45,990
It would.

829
01:07:47,780 --> 01:07:48,780
I see.

830
01:07:52,910 --> 01:07:54,160
I'll go with you.

831
01:07:55,870 --> 01:07:58,250
You'll get the chance
to apologize as well.

832
01:08:00,550 --> 01:08:01,550
Thank you.

833
01:08:16,940 --> 01:08:17,940
Mr. Cha Jeongho?

834
01:08:18,650 --> 01:08:19,690
Yes.

835
01:08:20,520 --> 01:08:21,530
Hello.

836
01:08:22,860 --> 01:08:23,860
I'm Cha Jeongho.

837
01:08:28,620 --> 01:08:29,620
I'm Ahn Juhyeong.

838
01:08:32,240 --> 01:08:35,410
We've agreed to divorce,

839
01:08:36,790 --> 01:08:41,590
but we're stuck on alimony
and splitting assets.

840
01:08:42,880 --> 01:08:44,880
Has a trial date been set?

841
01:08:44,970 --> 01:08:48,340
Yes, we couldn't settle,
so a trial date's been set.

842
01:08:48,430 --> 01:08:49,470
I mean,

843
01:08:50,260 --> 01:08:52,060
we figured buying lawyers

844
01:08:52,810 --> 01:08:54,730
would only make things messier,

845
01:08:55,680 --> 01:08:58,730
so we both agreed not to buy them.

846
01:08:59,480 --> 01:09:01,190
But at this point,

847
01:09:01,270 --> 01:09:04,820
I felt like I needed to do
what was best for me.

848
01:09:05,530 --> 01:09:06,780
You said you agreed

849
01:09:06,860 --> 01:09:09,240
-not to buy lawyers?
-Yes.

850
01:09:09,320 --> 01:09:11,240
Lawyers aren't things you buy and sell.

851
01:09:11,330 --> 01:09:12,330
Really?

852
01:09:14,620 --> 01:09:16,040
That's weird.

853
01:09:16,120 --> 01:09:18,960
I'm here today to buy a lawyer though.

854
01:09:22,840 --> 01:09:24,710
Yes, I see.

855
01:09:24,800 --> 01:09:26,920
Are you far apart on your terms?

856
01:09:27,010 --> 01:09:28,930
I can't give her a cent.

857
01:09:29,010 --> 01:09:32,760
Sure, I brought up
getting a divorce first,

858
01:09:33,850 --> 01:09:36,230
but that doesn't mean
I owe her money, right?

859
01:09:36,310 --> 01:09:38,060
Then, you don't need to pay alimony.

860
01:09:38,140 --> 01:09:39,850
I can't give away my assets either.

861
01:09:41,610 --> 01:09:43,020
We've only been married

862
01:09:43,770 --> 01:09:45,110
a little over a year.

863
01:09:45,900 --> 01:09:47,400
It hasn't been that long.

864
01:09:47,490 --> 01:09:50,450
None of my assets came from that marriage.

865
01:09:51,160 --> 01:09:54,910
I covered almost
all the wedding expenses myself.

866
01:09:54,990 --> 01:09:57,250
How much is the other party asking for?

867
01:09:58,580 --> 01:10:01,670
She wants 10 million won in alimony
and 10 million won in assets.

868
01:10:05,500 --> 01:10:07,720
Well, it's not actually a lot.

869
01:10:08,630 --> 01:10:11,300
She just wanted a symbolic number

870
01:10:11,390 --> 01:10:13,180
since I first proposed the divorce.

871
01:10:16,520 --> 01:10:19,850
You could've just agreed
and settled this divorce then.

872
01:10:20,770 --> 01:10:22,020
You're pretty well-off.

873
01:10:25,610 --> 01:10:26,610
Why should I?

874
01:10:28,820 --> 01:10:29,990
I'm not backing down.

875
01:10:30,070 --> 01:10:35,200
We call it personality differences,
but the divorce is basically her fault.

876
01:10:35,280 --> 01:10:37,450
So you're saying
she has cause for liability?

877
01:10:38,160 --> 01:10:40,910
Well, not technically
cause for liability, butâ€¦

878
01:10:45,840 --> 01:10:47,710
In any case, we're just incompatible.

879
01:10:48,300 --> 01:10:49,760
Totally incompatible.

880
01:10:50,550 --> 01:10:54,390
I'm losing my mind.
I can't live with her anymore.

881
01:10:54,470 --> 01:10:58,060
Also, it's all on her.

882
01:11:19,290 --> 01:11:24,580
NOTICE OF WITHDRAWAL
PLAINTIFF KIM SANGGU

883
01:11:52,690 --> 01:11:54,110
-What are you doing here?
-What?

884
01:11:55,280 --> 01:11:59,740
While heading out,
I was just checking if everyone had left.

885
01:11:59,830 --> 01:12:02,120
-Are you clocking out?
-Yeah, I am.

886
01:12:03,160 --> 01:12:05,500
You must be the last one here.

887
01:12:05,580 --> 01:12:07,750
Yeah, Juhyeong left early today.

888
01:12:08,670 --> 01:12:09,880
Really?

889
01:12:09,960 --> 01:12:10,960
Let's go.

890
01:12:11,050 --> 01:12:12,050
Okay.

